sequenceDiagram
    participant Admin as Administrator<br/>(kubectl / helm / ArgoCD)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OLM as OLM<br/>(Operator Lifecycle Manager)
    participant Catalog as CatalogSource<br/>50051/TCP gRPC TLS
    participant Registry as Container Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant NS as Target Namespace<br/>(Operator Deployment)
    participant Hook as Post-Install Hook Job
    participant CertMgr as cert-manager
    participant CloudMgr as Cloud Manager<br/>(Azure/CoreWeave/AWS)
    participant CloudAPI as Cloud Provider APIs<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
        Note over Admin,NS: Flow 1: Kustomize Deployment on OpenShift
        Admin->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply -k dependencies/<br/>Auth: kubeconfig / ServiceAccount
        K8sAPI->>OLM: Process Subscriptions<br/>Internal RBAC
        OLM->>Catalog: Query operator packages<br/>gRPC/50051 TLS
        OLM->>Registry: Pull operator images<br/>HTTPS/443 Pull Secret
        OLM->>NS: Deploy operator pods<br/>Internal RBAC
        Admin->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply -k configurations/<br/>Auth: kubeconfig
        Note right of K8sAPI: Creates Kueue, JobSet, LWS,<br/>Kuadrant, Authorino CRs
    end

    rect rgb(255, 243, 224)
        Note over Admin,CloudAPI: Flow 2: Helm Deployment on XKS (Vanilla Kubernetes)
        Admin->>K8sAPI: helm install rhai-on-xks-chart<br/>Auth: kubeconfig
        K8sAPI->>NS: Create redhat-ods-operator namespace<br/>Internal RBAC
        NS->>Registry: Pull RHAI operator image<br/>HTTPS/443 rhai-pull-secret
        Note right of NS: RHAI Operator starts<br/>9443/TCP webhook<br/>8080/TCP metrics<br/>8081/TCP health
        Hook->>K8sAPI: Create CRs (Kserve, KubernetesEngine)<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA: rhai-post-install-hook
        Hook->>K8sAPI: Create Gateway + GatewayClass<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA: rhai-post-install-hook
        CertMgr->>CertMgr: Issue rhai-ca + inference-gateway-cert<br/>ClusterIssuer: rhai-ca-issuer
        CloudMgr->>CloudAPI: Manage cloud infrastructure<br/>HTTPS/443 Cloud credentials
    end

    rect rgb(224, 255, 230)
        Note over Admin,NS: Flow 3: Inference Gateway Traffic (Post-Deployment)
        participant Client as External Client
        participant GW as Inference Gateway<br/>(Istio/Envoy)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
        participant KServe as KServe InferenceService<br/>mTLS (Istio)

        Client->>GW: Inference request<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS (inference-gateway-cert)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        GW->>KServe: Forward to HTTPRoute target<br/>HTTP/gRPC mTLS<br/>Auth: Authorino / kube-rbac-proxy
        KServe-->>GW: Prediction response
        GW-->>Client: JSON/gRPC response
    end
